In [68]:
tsc = sadhia['speeding'].sum()
tac = sadhia['alcohol'].sum()
toc = sadhia['total'].sum() - (tsc + tac)
labels = ['Speeding Crashes', 'Alcohol-Related Crashes', 'Other Crashes']
sizes = [tsc, tac, toc]
colors = ['blue', 'red', 'pink']
Explode=[0.1,0,0.2]
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))
plt.pie(sizes, labels=labels, colors=colors, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=140, explode=Explode)
plt.title('Distribution of Crashes by Category')
plt.show()
#Inference: we can say that as other reason crashes greater than the Alcohol related Crashes & speeding crashes.
